seal     : The 3DO was a specification, not a single product: Trip Hawkins's company licensed a CD-based design that Panasonic, Goldstar, and others built. An ARM CPU with twin custom video coprocessors made it powerful for 1993 — and a 699-dollar launch price made it a commercial cautionary tale.
